<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Zechariah on Christian Internet Resources</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/</link><description>Recent content in Zechariah on Christian Internet Resources</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Zechariah 1</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-01/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-01/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-1">Zechariah Chapter 1&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="conversational-yahveh-covenant">Conversational Yahveh Covenant&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-bottom:0in; text-align:center'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The
&lt;b>Eighth Month, Second Year of Darius&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-bottom:0in; text-align:center'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>A Message from Yahveh to the Prophet Zechariah Ben-Berechiah Ben-Iddo&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="a-call-to-return-to-yahveh">A Call to Return to Yahveh&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“I&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;i>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Y&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/i>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>was angry with your ancestors.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height: 115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>So tell the people, ‘Yahveh of hosts says, “Come back to me so I can come back to you. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Don’t be like your ancestors that former prophets told to come back from their sinful ways and deeds,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%; font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;i>but they didn’t pay any attention. &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Where are those ancestors? Prophets don’t live forever, &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>but my message commanded through them did come to bear on your ancestors. As a result, they repented and said, ‘Yahveh of hosts has dealt with us the way he intended, according to our ways and deeds.’”’”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Zechariah 2</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-02/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-02/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-2">Zechariah Chapter 2&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="a-man-with-a-measuring-line">A Man with a Measuring Line&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Then I saw a man holding a measuring line, and &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>asked him where he was going.&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;a name="_Hlk122962178">&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“To measure how wide and long&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;i>Jerusalem is.”&lt;/i> &lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The angel that was talking to me was leaving, and another angel met him &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>and said, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Run and tell that young man, ‘Jerusalem will be lived in like open country because of the number of people and livestock that’s in it. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I’ll be a fire wall around it and the glory in it. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Zechariah 3</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-03/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-03/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-3">Zechariah Chapter 3&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="the-cleansing-of-joshua-the-high-priest">The Cleansing of Joshua the High Priest&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Then he showed me Joshua/&lt;i>Jeshua&lt;/i> the high priest standing in front of the angel of Yahveh, and Satan standing to his right to accuse him. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Yahveh told Satan, &lt;i>“Yahveh rebuke you, Satan! I who chose Jerusalem reject your accusations! Isn’t this &lt;/i>man&lt;i> a brand snatched out of the fire?”&lt;/i> &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Joshua’s clothes were dirty, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>so the angel&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'> told the ones standing there, &lt;i>“Change his dirty clothes.” “I’ve taken your sinfulness off so I can dress you up with festive robes.”&lt;/i> &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Zechariah 4</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-04/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-04/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-4">Zechariah Chapter 4&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="zech-36-10">Zech 3:6-10&lt;/h3>
&lt;h3 id="a-lampstand-and-two-olive-trees">A Lampstand and Two Olive Trees&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The angel came back and brought me to as if I’d been asleep. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He asked me what I saw.&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>“A gold lampstand with its bowl &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>of oil &lt;i>on top, as well as its seven lamps with one spout apiece. &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I see an olive tree on each side of it. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>What do they mean, Sir?”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Zechariah 5</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-05/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-05/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-5">Zechariah Chapter 5&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="zech-48-14">Zech 4:8-14&lt;/h3>
&lt;h3 id="a-flying-scroll">A Flying Scroll&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Then I looked up and saw a flying scroll. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He said, &lt;i>“What do you see?”&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“A flying scroll, 15 by 30ft.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He told me, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;a name="_Hlk122963502">&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%; font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“It contains the words of the curse that’s over the whole world. Everyone that steals will be erased from one side. Everyone that swears &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%; font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>falsely &lt;i>will be erased from the other. &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Yahveh of Hosts will send the curse out to the thief’s house and to the house of the one that swears falsely by his name. The curse will remain there all night till it consumes its timbers and stones.’”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>         &lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Zech 5:1-4&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Zechariah 6</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-06/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-06/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-6">Zechariah Chapter 6&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="four-chariots">Four Chariots&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I looked again and saw four chariots coming out from between two bronze mountains. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Chestnut horses were pulling the first chariot, black horses the second, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>white horses the third, and powerful dappled-gray horses the fourth. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I asked the angel,
&lt;i>“What are they, Sir?” &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“They’re the four spirits of heaven going out from the Lord of the whole world. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>One
&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>chariot
&lt;i>is going north with the black horses; after them the white horses are going west. The dappled-gray horses are going south. &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v7" id="v7">&lt;sup class="verse-num">7&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Those powerful horses went out, chomping at the bit to patrol the world.” &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Zechariah 7</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-07/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-07/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-7">Zechariah Chapter 7&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-bottom:0in; text-align:center'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The
&lt;b>Fourth Day, Ninth Month (&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Chislev&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>), Fourth Year of King Darius&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-bottom:0in; text-align:center'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>A Message from Yahveh to Zechariah &lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="a-call-for-justice-and-mercy-not-fasting">A Call for Justice and Mercy, Not Fasting&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The people in Bethel had sent Sharezer, Regem-melech, and their men to ask for Yahveh’s blessing. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>They spoke to the priests in Yahveh’s Temple and to the prophets, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Zechariah 8</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-08/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-08/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-8">Zechariah Chapter 8&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-bottom:0in; text-align:center'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>A Message from Yahveh&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="promised-blessings-for-jerusalem">Promised Blessings for Jerusalem&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Yahveh of Hosts says, ‘I’m jealous for Zion. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I’ll come back to live in Jerusalem, and it’ll be called The City of Truth. My mountain will be called The Holy Mount. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Old men and women will sit in its streets again with staffs &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>in hand &lt;i>because they’re old. &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Boys and girls will play in the streets. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>If that sounds incredible to the remnant that’s left, does that make it incredible for me?  &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v7" id="v7">&lt;sup class="verse-num">7&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I’m going to save my people from lands east and west &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v8" id="v8">&lt;sup class="verse-num">8&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>and bring them back to live here. They’ll be my people, and I’ll be their God, faithful and just.’                                                                                         &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Zech 8:1-8&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>             &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Zechariah 9</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-09/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-09/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-9">Zechariah Chapter 9&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-bottom:0in; text-align:center'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>A Message from Yahveh Against the Land of Hadrach [&lt;i>Aram&lt;/i>]&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>The message from Yahveh is against Damascus—for the eyes of all people, including&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>
&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>the tribes of Israel, are on Yahveh—&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>against Hamath, which borders it,&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>and against Tyre and Sidon, though they’re so very wise.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Tyre built a fortress,&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Zechariah 10</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-10/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-10/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-10">Zechariah Chapter 10&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="yahveh-will-restore-his-people">Yahveh Will Restore His People&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;a name="_Hlk122970802">&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;/a>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Ask Yahveh for showers in the spring;&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      the One that forms the storm clouds&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            will give each &lt;i>farmer&lt;/i> crops in his field.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Household gods speak nonsense;&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      fortunetellers see false dreams&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            and give empty consolation.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>So people wander in danger like lost sheep &lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Zechariah 11</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-11/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-11/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-11">Zechariah Chapter 11&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="good-and-bad-shepherds">Good and Bad Shepherds&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Open your doors, Lebanon,&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      so fire can consume your cedar forests.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Wail, cypress trees, for the fallen cedars;&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      The stately trees have burned up.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Wail, oaks of Bashan;&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>      the thick woodland has been cut down.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The shepherds wail &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Zechariah 12</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-12/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-12/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-12">Zechariah Chapter 12&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-bottom:0in; text-align:center'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>A Message from Yahveh About Israel&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="future-destruction-of-jerusalems-enemies">Future Destruction of Jerusalem’s Enemies&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>This is what Yahveh says who stretched out the sky, laid earth’s foundation, and formed the human spirit:&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;a name="_Hlk122971722">&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;/a>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“I’m going to make Jerusalem a cup that makes every nation stagger who lays siege to Jerusalem and Judah. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I’ll make Jerusalem a heavy rock; any &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>nation&lt;i> that tries to pick it up will rupture itself. When nations surround it, &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I’ll make their horses bolt and their riders panic, but I’ll watch over Judah as I strike those enemies’ horses blind. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;b>&lt;i>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>5&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/i>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The clans in Judah will realize that the residents of Jerusalem have strong protection from Yahveh of Hosts their God.’&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:10.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>       Zech 12:1-5&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>
&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Zechariah 13</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-13/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-13/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-13">Zechariah Chapter 13&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="the-cleansing-fountain">The Cleansing Fountain&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Then a fountain will spring up for David’s house and the people in Jerusalem, &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>a fountain &lt;i>for &lt;/i>cleansing&lt;i> sin and impurity. &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I’ll get rid of the idols in Israel; they’ll fade from memory. I’ll remove &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>false&lt;i> prophets and unclean spirits. &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>If anybody still tries to make up their own prophecy, their own parents will say, ‘You’ve lied in Yahveh’s name!’ and they’ll run them through. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>People will be averse to claiming they’ve had visions; they won’t put on a &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>prophet’s
&lt;i>hairy robe to create impressions&lt;a name="_Hlk122972579">. &lt;/a>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>They’ll say, ‘I’m not a prophet; I plow ground because a man sold me as a slave when I was a kid.’ &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>If somebody asks him, ‘Where did those scars come from around your wrists?’ he’ll say, ‘From wounds at “a friend’s” house!’&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size: 10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>     Zech 13:1-6&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Zechariah 14</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-14/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/zechariah/chapter-14/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zechariah-chapter-14">Zechariah Chapter 14&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="yahveh-will-rule-the-world">Yahveh Will Rule the World&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Yahveh will bring a time when nations will plunder you right in front of you. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He’ll gather them against Jerusalem and capture it. The houses will be looted and the women raped; half the people will be exiled and the rest abandoned among the ruins.  &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>But then Yahveh&lt;i> wi&lt;/i>ll go out and fight them. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>His feet will stand on the Mount of Olives east of Jerusalem. The mountain will split apart east to west, half moving north and half moving south with a wide valley between. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>You’ll escape by that valley, which will reach as far as Azal. You’ll flee like you did from the earthquake when Uzziah reigned in Judah. Then Yahveh my God will come with his holy ones! &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>There won’t be any cold or frost, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v7" id="v7">&lt;sup class="verse-num">7&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>a unique day known
&lt;i>only &lt;/i>to Yahveh, without day or night; there’ll be light in the evening. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v8" id="v8">&lt;sup class="verse-num">8&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>At that time, water will pour out of Jerusalem year around, half to the Dead Sea and half to the Mediterranean.&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>